HEADWORD: Sampan
<hw>Sam"pan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A Chinese boat from twelve to fifteen feet long, covered with a
house, and sometimes used as a permanent habitation on the inland
waters.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>sanpan</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Samphire</ent>⟦br⟧
